"title": "5716: middle age",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5716",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The period between youth and old age. Middle age is marked by physical strength and experience and should bring maturity and stability. Many of God's servants began ministry in middle age, often after having been prepared in their youth. Middle age may also bring complacency and the temptation to leave the devotion and commitments of youth.</p>\n<h2>Middle age defined</h2>\n<h3>Adulthood reckoned from age 20</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:2-Num1:3\">NUM 1:2–1:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:14\">EXO 30:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod38:26\">EXO 38:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num26:2-Num26:4\">NUM 26:2–26:4</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:24\">1CH 23:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr31:17\">2CH 31:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra3:8\">EZR 3:8</a></p>\n<h3>Full maturity reckoned from age 30</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:23\">LUK 3:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:30\">NUM 4:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:43\">NUM 4:43</a></p>\n<h2>Characteristics of middle age</h2>\n<h3>Physical strength</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:3-Lev27:7\">LEV 27:3–27:7</a></strong> <em>Strength is greatest between 20 and 60.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:45\">NUM 1:45</a> <em>Men served in the army from age 20</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh14:10\">JOS 14:10</a> <em>Caleb, in his prime at 40, is still strong at 85.</em></p>\n<h3>Growth in wisdom and experience</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl1:16\">ECC 1:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:33\">1SA 17:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam17:8\">2SA 17:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr17:13\">2CH 17:13</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr22:5\">1CH 22:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:1\">1CH 29:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:7\">PRO 7:7</a></p>\n<h3>Maturity and stability</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:13-Eph4:14\">EPH 4:13–4:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:6\">1CO 2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:11-Heb5:14\">HEB 5:11–5:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:4\">JAS 1:4</a></p>\n<h2>The responsibilities of middle age</h2>\n<h3>The need to be prepared for these responsibilities</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:6\">PRO 22:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov4:1-Prov4:4\">PRO 4:1–4:4</a> <em>Solomon passes on wisdom learned from his father.</em><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:80\">LUK 1:80</a></strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:26\">1SA 2:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:40\">LUK 2:40</a></p>\n<h3>The need to train for service</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num8:24\">NUM 8:24</a></strong> <em>The period from 25 to 30 (see <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:3\">Nu 4:3</a>) may have been a period of apprenticeship.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:27\">1CH 23:27</a> <em>In later years the apprenticeship may have started at 20</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:28\">NUM 11:28</a></p>\n<h3>The start of service in middle age</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:3\">NUM 4:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:23\">ACT 7:23</a> <em>Moses showed concern for his fellow Israelites at age 40</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh14:7\">JOS 14:7</a> <em>Caleb was 40 when he explored Canaan</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam7:3-1Sam7:4\">1SA 7:3–7:4</a> <em>Samuel became judge over Israel in his thirties</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:3\">LUK 3:3</a> <em>John the Baptist began his public ministry at about 30</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:57\">JHN 8:57</a> <em>Jesus Christ had not achieved the status of wisdom and authority associated with old age in Israel</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:1-1Tim3:13\">1TI 3:1–3:13</a> <em>The mention of families in the instructions to elders and deacons suggests that these leaders were of middle age.</em></p>\n<h3>Rulers coming to office in middle age</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:46\">GEN 41:46</a> <em>Joseph</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:1\">1SA 13:1</a> <em>Saul</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:4\">2SA 5:4</a> <em>David</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:10\">2SA 2:10</a> <em>Ish-Bosheth</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr12:13\">2CH 12:13</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:21\">1KI 14:21</a> <em>Rehoboam</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:31\">2CH 20:31</a> <em>Jehoshaphat</em></p>\n<h2>Temptations of middle age</h2>\n<h3>Complacency</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:1\">2SA 11:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa32:9-Isa32:11\">ISA 32:9–32:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos6:1\">AMO 6:1</a></p>\n<h3>Worldly distractions</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:4\">2SA 11:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:3-1Kgs11:4\">1KI 11:3–11:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:1-Eccl2:8\">ECC 2:1–2:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:18-Luke12:19\">LUK 12:18–12:19</a></p>\n<h3>Turning from the commitment of youth</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov2:16-Prov2:17\">PRO 2:16–2:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:14\">MAL 2:14</a></p>",
